description:
DEPENDENCIES: Install `sharp` as dev dependency if not present: `cd website && npm install -D sharp @types/node`

FILES TO CREATE:
- `website/scripts/generate-blur-data.ts` - Script to generate blur data URLs

FILES TO MODIFY:
- `website/src/lib/data.ts` - Add `blurDataURL: string` field to each gallery item in the array
- `website/src/app/gallery/page.tsx` - Add `placeholder="blur"` and `blurDataURL={item.blurDataURL}` props to Image components

IMPLEMENTATION:
1. Create `generate-blur-data.ts` script:
```typescript
import sharp from 'sharp';
import fs from 'fs';
import path from 'path';

const galleryDir = path.join(__dirname, '../public/gallery');
const dataFilePath = path.join(__dirname, '../src/lib/data.ts');

async function generateBlurData() {
  const images = fs.readdirSync(galleryDir).filter(f => f.endsWith('.webp'));
  const blurMap: Record<string, string> = {};

  for (const img of images) {
    const buffer = await sharp(path.join(galleryDir, img))
      .resize(10) // 10px width, auto height
      .webp({ quality: 20 })
      .toBuffer();
    blurMap[`/gallery/${img}`] = `data:image/webp;base64,${buffer.toString('base64')}`;
  }

  // Output JSON for manual insertion into data.ts
  console.log(JSON.stringify(blurMap, null, 2));
}
```
2. Run script: `ts-node website/scripts/generate-blur-data.ts > blur-data.json`
3. Manually merge blur data into `data.ts` gallery array, OR modify script to auto-update data.ts via AST manipulation
4. Update Image components to use blur placeholders:
```tsx
<Image
  {...existingProps}
  placeholder="blur"
  blurDataURL={item.blurDataURL}
/>
```

ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA:
- Every gallery item in `data.ts` has a valid `blurDataURL` field (base64-encoded, ~1-2KB each)
- All Image components in gallery have `placeholder="blur"` prop
- Visual test: gallery images show blurred preview before full image loads (test on throttled network)
- No console errors about missing blur data
- Blur data URLs are under 2KB each (inspect data.ts file size increase)
- Script is reusable - can regenerate blur data after adding new images
